<subSubSection id="9312ACAF5859716C522B6AB540961716" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="AF569719FE2607C6DDCB1245B9B10BA4" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2AB271199FA308E0D171451AD4532063" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
A Euro-Siberian floristic element reported twice in Greece: on the high-altitude serpentine rocks of Mt. Smolikas (
<bibRefCitation id="CC18E5159F10CB4BBE5786B143C9D9BF" author="Lack, H. W." journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh University Press, Edinburg" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668868" refString="Lack, H. W., Kilian, N., 1991. Mountain Flora of Greece 2. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburg" title="Mountain Flora of Greece 2" year="1991">Lack and Kilian 1991</bibRefCitation>
) and on the northern foothills of Mt. Olimbos (
<bibRefCitation id="60A187167E3DCC74AE8C180D8AD643CA" author="Strid, A." journalOrPublisher="Willdenowia" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="329 - 333" refId="B7669458" refString="Strid, A., Franzen, R., 1984. Chromosome numbers in flowering plants from Greece. Willdenowia 13 (2): 329 - 333" title="Chromosome numbers in flowering plants from Greece" volume="13" year="1984">
Strid and 
<normalizedToken id="FDADAE4DBEA03D921DB00B84EA1CD158" originalValue="Franzén">Franzen</normalizedToken>
1984
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="B868CB1723919E8CBFEB3BA0B838E8CC" author="Lack, H. W." journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh University Press, Edinburg" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668868" refString="Lack, H. W., Kilian, N., 1991. Mountain Flora of Greece 2. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburg" title="Mountain Flora of Greece 2" year="1991">Lack and Kilian (1991)</bibRefCitation>
recorded the species as 
<taxonomicName id="3E31C72CBD212DCCB83BDE623BFE0218" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Scorzonera" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scorzonera austriaca" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austriaca">
<emphasis id="2B5130D07B50C6048DAA34E20E9981D1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Scorzonera austriaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and noted that the Mt. Smolikas population is somehow intermediate between subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="320C6E8687256503B25CE702F3021E96" authority="austriaca" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Scorzonera" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scorzonera austriaca subsp. austriaca" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="austriaca" subSpecies="austriaca">Scorzonera austriaca austriaca</taxonomicName>
and subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="D4CF72184715834E3B76D6A7A12C984C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Scorzonera" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scorzonera austriaca subsp. bupleurifolia" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="austriaca" subSpecies="bupleurifolia">Scorzonera austriaca bupleurifolia</taxonomicName>
(Pouzolz) Bonnier. The Mt. Achladovouno population (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E7E845F12EA96F0C886CA377CEA2C4E6" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F7677578" captionText="Figure 9. Takhtajaniantha austriaca from Mt. Achladovouno (photo: P. Doumas)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/640535" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">9</figureCitation>
) is new for the NE region and comes closer to the typical subspecies because of its basal leaves with lamina gradually narrowed into the petiole (
<bibRefCitation id="DF25513308D0C784248B6919B4BF5C88" author="Chater, A. O." journalOrPublisher="Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667950" refString="Chater, A. O., 1976. Flora Europaea Vol. 4. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" title="Flora Europaea Vol. 4" year="1976">Chater 1976</bibRefCitation>
). Nomenclature follows 
<bibRefCitation id="E6187388B211467E35CFFCC5D9435C19" author="Zaika, M. A." journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="1 - 85" refId="B7670241" refString="Zaika, M. A., Kilian, N., Jones, K., Krinitsina, A. A., Nilova, M. V., Speranskaya, A. S., Sukhorukov, A. P., 2020. Scorzonera sensu lato (Asteraceae, Cichorieae) - taxonomic reassessment in the light of new molecular phylogenetic and carpological analyses. PhytoKeys 137: 1 - 85" title="Scorzonera sensu lato (Asteraceae, Cichorieae) - taxonomic reassessment in the light of new molecular phylogenetic and carpological analyses" volume="137" year="2020">Zaika et al. (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, who transferred 
<taxonomicName id="959BEC2EFFD699551AEE2F5BF1E0CA8A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Scorzonera" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scorzonera austriaca" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austriaca">
<emphasis id="957A83D01BD5B6C3F9503FF7A8233561" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Scorzonera austriaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="A6B170C942EAAD6E9693694B1654306B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Takhtajaniantha" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Takhtajaniantha" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E46A08F44C6A697D909C504268A342E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Takhtajaniantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in accordance with carpological, anatomical and molecular phylogenetic evidence.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
